---

<BaseLayout
  title="PH Gaming Intel — Philippines Gaming Industry News & Analysis"
  description="PH Gaming Intel covers the Philippines gaming industry with in-depth news, regulatory analysis, PAGCOR updates, POGO tracking, and IR resort coverage."
  activePage="news"
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

  <!-- HERO — Featured Story -->
  <section class="hero-featured" aria-label="Featured story">
    <img src="/hero/pasay-to-sihanoukville-worker-migration.png"
         alt="A POGO worker's migration from Pasay to Sihanoukville — layered map and silhouettes"
         width="1920" height="1080" loading="eager">
    <div class="overlay">
      <div class="overlay-inner">
        <span class="tag tag-longread">Longread</span>
        <h1>From Pasay to Sihanoukville: A POGO Worker's Migration</h1>
        <p class="dek">When the Philippine offshore gaming industry was shut down in 2024, the buildings emptied. The workers had to go somewhere. A reconstructed account of one path — and what the journey reveals about a regional labor market in transition.</p>
        <p class="meta">May 27, 2026 &middot; 22 min read &middot; Editorial Score 10/10</p>
        <a href="/articles/pasay-to-sihanoukville-worker-migration.html" style="display:inline-block;margin-top:16px;padding:12px 28px;border-radius:8px;background:var(--gold);color:var(--dark);font-family:var(--font-ui);font-size:14px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.5px;transition:background .2s;">Read the Full Story</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- LATEST NEWS -->
  <section class="mt-section mb-section" id="latest-news" aria-label="Latest news">
    <div class="section-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-title">Latest News</h2>
      <div class="card-grid">

        <a href="/articles/pagcor-2026-ggr-forecast-cut-19-percent-online-slowdown" class="card">
          <div class="card-img">
            <img src="/hero/pagcor-2026-ggr-forecast-cut-19-percent-online-slowdown.png"
                 alt="A descending revenue line over a stylised casino floor and phone, one column held up by tourism while the online column sinks"
                 width="640" height="360" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <span class="tag tag-news">News</span>
            <h3>PAGCOR Cuts Its 2026 Revenue Forecast: Why the Regulator Now Expects GGR to Fall as Much as 19%</h3>
            <p class="card-dek">In early June, chairman Alejandro Tengco said industry GGR could fall up to 19% this year — to ₱320–350B, down from ₱396.14B in 2025 — a sharp reversal from February's flat projection. The damage is concentrated online, where e-wallet delinking cut electronic-gaming revenue 22% in Q1. Why a falling top line is partly the tightening working as designed — and the one figure it can't see.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">June 15, 2026 &middot; Score 9/10</p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/articles/philippines-influencer-prosecution-illegal-gambling-promoters-2026" class="card">
          <div class="card-img">
            <img src="/hero/philippines-influencer-prosecution-illegal-gambling-promoters-2026.png"
                 alt="A glowing megaphone casting a betting-site shadow, with a legal seal and handcuff motif closing in from the edges"
                 width="640" height="360" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <span class="tag tag-news">News</span>
            <h3>From Blocking Sites to Charging People: The Philippines Turns Its Crackdown on Promoters and Influencers</h3>
            <p class="card-dek">After years of blocking sites and cutting payment rails, the CICC — with PAGCOR and Digital Pinoys — moved to charge the influencers who funnel audiences to illegal betting platforms, naming figures like Jam Magno. 1,891 complaints in two months, the 2012 Cybercrime law, a CICC–PAOCC case-buildup pact, and Meta takedowns. Why the target shifted to people — and where it could overreach.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">June 15, 2026 &middot; Score 9/10</p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <a href="/articles/world-cup-2026-crypto-betting-scams-tracing-philippines" class="card">
          <div class="card-img">
            <img src="/hero/world-cup-2026-crypto-betting-scams-tracing-philippines.png"
                 alt="Glowing transaction trails leaving fake betting sites and threading through a bridge structure, with a magnifier following the brightest thread"
                 width="640" height="360" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <span class="tag tag-news">News</span>
            <h3>Following the Crypto: How Blockchain Trackers Are Watching World Cup Betting Scams Take Shape</h3>
            <p class="card-dek">TRM Labs is tracing the on-chain footprint of World Cup fraud — fake ticketing sites, fan meme coins, fixed-match pitches — with proceeds routed through cross-chain bridges. The amounts captured so far are tiny because the scams are still warming up. For Filipinos, the crypto angle is the tell: it's the exact rail the payment crackdown pushed offshore betting toward. How to read a crypto pitch before it reads your wallet.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">June 12, 2026 &middot; Score 9/10</p>
          </div>
        </a>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SPORTS BETTING — World Cup 2026 -->
  <section class="mb-section" id="sports-betting" aria-label="Sports betting and the World Cup">
    <div class="section-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-title">Sports Betting &middot; World Cup 2026 &nbsp;<a href="/sports-betting" style="font-size:14px;font-family:var(--font-ui);font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.5px;color:var(--gold);text-transform:uppercase;vertical-align:middle;">View all &rsaquo;</a></h2>
      <div class="card-grid-2">

        <a href="/articles/how-to-watch-world-cup-2026-philippines-legal-free-paid" class="card card-lg">
          <div class="card-img">
            <img src="/hero/how-to-watch-world-cup-2026-philippines-legal-free-paid.png"
                 alt="Legal ways to watch the 2026 World Cup in the Philippines, free and paid"
                 width="640" height="360" loading="lazy">
          </div>
          <div class="card-body">
            <span class="tag tag-guide">Guide</span>
            <h3>How to Watch the 2026 World Cup in the Philippines — Legally, Free and Paid</h3>
            <p class="card-dek">Officially distributed through Aleph Group: BlastTV carries every match on pay-per-view (FIFA World Cup Pass ~PHP 1,999), with select games free on Aleph Arena YouTube, GMA, and TV5. With kickoff around 3 AM Manila time, chasing unofficial streams is exactly what malware operators count on. The licensed way to watch all 104 matches — and the traps to avoid.</p>
            <p class="card-meta">June 5, 2026 &middot; 7 min read</p>
          </div>
        </a>

        <div class="card-stack">
          <a href="/articles/world-cup-2026-age-verification-underage-gambling-kyc" class="card-row">
            <div class="card-img">
              <img src="/hero/world-cup-2026-age-verification-underage-gambling-kyc.png"
                   alt="Age and identity verification keeping minors out of online betting during the World Cup"
                   width="200" height="150" loading="lazy">
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
              <span class="tag tag-news">News</span>
              <h3>The World Cup Will Be the Biggest Test Yet of Whether Betting Apps Can Keep Minors Out</h3>
              <p class="card-meta">June 5, 2026 &middot; 8 min read</p>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a href="/tools/responsible-gambling-self-assessment" class="card-row">
            <div class="card-img">
              <img src="/hero/responsible-gambling-self-assessment.png"
                   alt="Private responsible-gambling self-assessment based on the Problem Gambling Severity Index"
                   width="200" height="150" loading="lazy">
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
              <span class="tag" style="background:var(--gold);color:var(--dark);">Tool</span>
              <h3>New Tool: Responsible Gambling Self-Assessment (PGSI)</h3>
              <p class="card-meta">Private &middot; 9 questions &middot; Know your risk</p>
            </div>
          </a>

          <a href="/tools/betting-odds-calculator" class="card-row">
            <div class="card-img">
              <img src="/hero/betting-odds-calculator.png"
                   alt="Free betting odds and implied probability calculator tool"
                   width="200" height="150" loading="lazy">
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
              <span class="tag" style="background:var(--gold);color:var(--dark);">Tool</span>
              <h3>Free Tool: Betting Odds &amp; Implied Probability Calculator</h3>
              <p class="card-meta">Interactive &middot; See the house margin</p>
            </div>
          </a>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ANALYSIS & GUIDES -->
  <section class="mb-section" id="analysis-guides" aria-label="Analysis and guides">
    <div class="section-wrap">
      <h2 class="section-title">Analysis &amp; Guides</h2>
      <div class="card-grid-2">

        <a href="/articles/senate-bill-47-anti-online-gambling-act-advertising-ban-penalties" class="card card-lg">
          <div class="card-img">
            <img src="/hero/senate-bill-47-anti-online-gambling-act-advertising-ban-penalties.png"
